{{Infobox officeholder | name = Majd ad-Dīn Ibn Athir | order = [[Emir of Mosul]] | birth_date = 1149 | birth_place = [[Jazīrat Ibn ʿUmar]], [[Turkey]] | death_date = 1210 | death_place = [[Mosul]] | relatives = {{plainlist| * [[Ali ibn al-Athir]] * [[Diyā' ad-Dīn]] }} }}
'''Majd ad-Dīn Ibn Athir''' (1149–1210)<ref>{{cite web |url=http://english.irib.ir/radioislam/programs/history-of-islam/item/84675-today-in-islamic-history-30th-of-zil-hijjah |title=Today in Islamic History (30th of Zil-Hijjah) |archive-url=https://archive.is/5T25K |archive-date=July 2, 2013 |date=November 15, 2012 |work=[[Radio Islam]] |access-date=April 12, 2018}}</ref> was a [[Kurdish people|Kurdish]] [[historian]], [[biographer]] and [[lexicographer]].<ref>{{cite book |first=Michael M. |last=Gunter |chapter=The A to Z of the Kurds |publisher=[[Scarecrow Press]] |date=January 22, 2009 |isbn=978-0-8108-6334-7 |url=https://books.google.com.tr/books?id=gbmTlG4_QxAC&pg=PA127 |page=127 |title=Kurdish historian and biographer Ibn al-Athir wrote in Arabic...}}</ref>
Majd ad-Din was the brother of [[Ali ibn al-Athir]] and [[Diyā' ad-Dīn]], also historian. He was [[emir of Mosul]] and lasted more than his brothers. He was a distinguished [[translator]] of the islamic language.
His dictionary ''Kitāb an-Ni/zdya''<ref>{{cite book |last=Ibn Athir |first=Majd ad-Dīn |title=Ibn Khallikan's Biographical Dictionary |translator-first=Bn. Mac Guckin |translator-last=De Slane |year=1843 |volume=1 |url=https://books.google.es/books?id=xPnqvmzhsMcC&pg=PA551 |page=551}}</ref> was published in [[El Cairo]] in 1893, and his dictionary ''Kitāb ul-Murassa'', about names of different families, was published by Ferdinand Seybold in [[Weimar]] in 1896.{{sfn|Weimar|1896}}
