'''Mihailo Dinić''' ({{lang-sr-cyr|Михаило Динић}}; 23 April 1899 – 12 May 1970) was a [[Serbia]]n historian and member of the [[Serbian Academy of Science and Arts]].<ref>{{cite book|title=Anali|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=GxwxAQAAIAAJ|accessdate=11 September 2013|year=1952|publisher=Institut|page=488|quote=...dr. Mihailo Dinić, akademik Srpske akademije nauka, redovni profesor Filozofskog fakulteta Univerziteta u Beogradu...}}</ref> He was among the key figures of the Serbian historiography of the 20th century.<ref>{{cite web|title=Iz srpske istorije srednjeg veka|url=http://www.knjizara.com/knjige/knjiga/92499_Iz+srpske+istorije+srednjeg+veka_ISBN 86-82937-07-7|publisher=knjizara.com|accessdate=15 September 2013}}</ref>

He was among many notable scholars in Serbia who bequeathed their personal libraries to the [[National Library of Serbia]].<ref>{{cite news|title= Velikani Narodnoj biblioteci zaveštali knjige, rukopise, lične stvari|url=http://www.novosti.rs/vesti/kultura.71.html:422290-Velikani-Narodnoj-biblioteci-zavestali-knjige-rukopise-licne-stvari|accessdate=15 September 2013|newspaper=Večernje Novosti|date=3 March 2013|language=Serbian}}</ref>

